President Cyril Ramaphosa announced changes to the national executive on Monday which saw him appoint ANC deputy president Paul Mashatile as his second in command  and former Tshwane mayor Kgosientso "Sputla" Ramokgopa as electricity minister. Mashatile is replacing former deputy president David Mabuza. Below is the full unedited speech of Ramaphosa's cabinet reconfiguration. IN FULL | Newly appointed cabinet ministers TimesLIVE